Acom Co., a Japanese consumer
lender, plunged the most in 20 months in Tokyo trading after the
Nikkei newspaper reported Takefuji Corp. is preparing to file
for bankruptcy protection.  Acom dropped 9.2 percent to 1,357 yen as of 9:07 a.m. on
the Tokyo Stock Exchange, headed for the biggest decline since
January 2009. Shares of Promise Co. were untraded and bid at 744
